African Rainbow Workers Start a Strike at Nkomati Nickel Mine, Union Says

-- B y   J a n a   M a r a i s
-- 
2011-08-29T06:15:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-29/african-rainbow-workers-start-a-strike-at-nkomati-nickel-mine-union-says.html
African Rainbow Minerals Ltd. (ARI) 
workers at the company’s Nkomati nickel mine started a strike
over wages and shift allowances today, National Union of
Mineworkers spokesman  Lesiba Seshoka  said.  The union expected “total closure” of the mine, Seshoka
said by mobile phone today. The company is offering an increase
of 4 percent on shift allowances while the union is demanding a
7 percent raise.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jana Marais in Johannesburg at 
 jmarais@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ana Monteiro at 
 amonteiro4@bloomberg.net  